{
  "global": "Solve for the angular frequency of small oscillations of an elliptical object rolling without slipping by calculating the effective radius of curvature, moment of inertia, and applying the rigid-body rocking equation.",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "subtask": "Establish the geometry of the elliptical cross-section and determine the radius of curvature at the contact point",
      "atomics": [
        "Parameterize the elliptical cross-section as (A cos t, B sin t) with semi-major axis A and semi-minor axis B",
        "Compute the radius of curvature using ρ(t) = (A²B²) / ((A² sin² t + B² cos² t)^(3/2))",
        "Evaluate at equilibrium contact point (t = 0) to get ρ = A²/B"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Calculate the moment of inertia of the elliptical object about its center of mass",
      "atomics": [
        "Apply the formula for moment of inertia of a uniform elliptical lamina perpendicular to the elliptical plane",
        "Compute I_cm = (m/4)(A² + B²) for rotation about the central axis"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Set up the equation of motion for a rigid body rolling without slipping on a curved surface",
      "atomics": [
        "Apply the rolling constraint: v_cm = ω_rotation × ρ",
        "Use energy conservation to write the Lagrangian with kinetic and potential energy terms",
        "Account for height variation Δh(θ) ≈ (ρ/2)θ² for small angular displacement θ",
        "Derive the equation of motion: θ̈ + (g ρ m)/(I_cm + m ρ²) θ = 0"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Extract the angular frequency from the harmonic oscillator equation",
      "atomics": [
        "Identify the angular frequency coefficient ω² = (g ρ m)/(I_cm + m ρ²) = g ρ / (I_cm/m + ρ²)",
        "Substitute ρ = A²/B and I_cm/m = (1/4)(A² + B²)",
        "Simplify the denominator: (1/4)(A² + B²) + (A⁴/B²) = (A²B² + B⁴ + 4A⁴)/(4B²)",
        "Obtain ω² = 4g A²/(4A⁴ + A²B² + B⁴)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Compute the final angular frequency and verify dimensional correctness",
      "atomics": [
        "Take the square root to get ω = √(4g A²/(4A⁴ + A²B² + B⁴))",
        "Verify dimensions: [g A²/(4A⁴ + A²B² + B⁴)] = [LT⁻²][L²]/[L⁴] = [T⁻²], so ω has dimension [T⁻¹] ✓"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "global_atomics": [
    "Check limiting case B → A: ω → √(2g/3A), which matches a symmetric elliptical object",
    "Confirm that ω is independent of mass m, consistent with the equivalence principle for gravitational systems"
  ],
  "gold_actions": {
    "global": "Compute the angular frequency of small-amplitude rolling oscillations on an elliptical surface by combining radius-of-curvature geometry, rotational inertia, and energy-based dynamics.",
    "subtasks": [
      {
        "subtask": "Compute the radius of curvature ρ at the equilibrium contact point where the ellipse rests stably",
        "atomics": [
          "Evaluate ρ = A²/B from the ellipse curvature formula at t = 0"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Calculate the moment of inertia I_cm = (m/4)(A² + B²) for the elliptical cross-section",
        "atomics": [
          "Use the standard formula for a uniform elliptical disk"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Derive the equation of motion θ̈ + (g ρ m)/(I_cm + m ρ²) θ = 0 using Lagrangian mechanics with rolling constraint and curvature-induced potential energy",
        "atomics": [
          "Set up L = KE - PE = (1/2)(I_cm + m ρ²)θ̇² - (1/2)m g ρ θ²",
          "Apply Euler-Lagrange equation to obtain the differential equation"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Extract ω² = g(A²/B) / ((1/4)(A² + B²) + A⁴/B²) and simplify to ω² = 4g A²/(4A⁴ + A²B² + B⁴)",
        "atomics": [
          "Substitute ρ and I_cm/m into the harmonic oscillator coefficient",
          "Multiply through by B² and simplify algebraically"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Compute the final result ω = √(4g A²/(4A⁴ + A²B² + B⁴)) = 2A√(g/(4A⁴ + A²B² + B⁴))",
        "atomics": [
          "Take the square root of the coefficient"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "global_atomics": [
      "Verify ω has dimension [T⁻¹]",
      "Confirm ω is independent of mass m"
    ]
  }
}
```

